    "This is also possible in (2.22) in order to obtain (2.12) in the limit: indeed, the inclusion in (2.12) results as a consequence of (2.38) and the maximal monotonicity of ∂F 1, since we can apply, e.g., [3, Prop. 2.2, p. 38].",
    "Finally, the initial conditions (2.14) can be readily obtained by observing that we have at least strong convergence in C 0 ([0, T]; V *) for all of the variables µ ε, ∂ t µ ε, φ ε, σ ε.",
    "With this, the existence part of the proof is complete.",
    "Uniqueness and Continuous Dependence:We now show the continuous dependence estimate (2.18), which implies the uniqueness of the solution, in particular.",
